# Git Commit — No Cursor Co-authored-by

Never add **Co-authored-by** (or any other trailer) attributing Cursor or the agent to commit messages.

## Forbidden

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- Any variant (different casing, spacing, or email) that credits Cursor/agent as co-author

## Required

- Commit messages contain only the human-authored summary/body the user expects.
- When using HEREDOC or `-m` for `git commit`, do not append Co-authored-by lines.
- If a hook or tool auto-injects such a trailer, do not add another; inform the user if it persists.

## Examples

```
# BAD
fix: correct stock calculation

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>

# GOOD
fix: correct stock calculation
```
